## 🟡 Medium Priority Improvements

### 1. Database Round-Trips on Every API Call (Performance)
* **File:** [JwtAuthenticationFilter.java](file:///c:/Users/YashRanjan/Desktop/Software%20Consulting/03_Projects/enterprise-asset-management-system/backend/src/main/java/com/yashconsulting/eams/security/JwtAuthenticationFilter.java#L45)
* **Description:** 
  The filter executes `userDetailsService.loadUserByUsername(userEmail)` for every authenticated request. This triggers a synchronous database query to retrieve user details from Postgres. This creates a severe performance bottleneck.
* **Recommendation:** Store basic security context (like the user's role and active state) as custom claims inside the signed JWT. Since the JWT is signed with a secret, the filter can parse and trust the authorities in the token without querying the database for every single request, or implement caching.

### 2. Missing Java 21 Record Classes (DTO Modernization)
* **Files:** All DTO classes (e.g. [LoginRequest.java](file:///c:/Users/YashRanjan/Desktop/Software%20Consulting/03_Projects/enterprise-asset-management-system/backend/src/main/java/com/yashconsulting/eams/auth/dto/LoginRequest.java), [UserResponse.java](file:///c:/Users/YashRanjan/Desktop/Software%20Consulting/03_Projects/enterprise-asset-management-system/backend/src/main/java/com/yashconsulting/eams/user/dto/UserResponse.java)) and exception schemas.
* **Description:** 
  DTOs are currently defined as traditional classes annotated with Lombok boilerplate (`@Getter @Setter @NoArgsConstructor @AllArgsConstructor @Builder`). In Java 21, immutable data carriers should be defined as `record` classes, eliminating Lombok code generator overhead, improving type safety, and ensuring immutability.
* **Recommendation:** Convert DTO structures to Java 21 `record` classes.

### 3. Redundant Public Path Bypass Duplication
* **Files:** [SecurityConfig.java](file:///c:/Users/YashRanjan/Desktop/Software%20Consulting/03_Projects/enterprise-asset-management-system/backend/src/main/java/com/yashconsulting/eams/config/SecurityConfig.java#L55-L61) and [JwtAuthenticationFilter.java](file:///c:/Users/YashRanjan/Desktop/Software%20Consulting/03_Projects/enterprise-asset-management-system/backend/src/main/java/com/yashconsulting/eams/security/JwtAuthenticationFilter.java#L61-L68)
* **Description:** 
  The list of permitAll endpoints (like `/api/v1/auth/**` and swagger paths) is defined twice. Overriding `shouldNotFilter` in the JWT filter is unnecessary because the filter already early-returns when the `Authorization` header is missing. Keeping this method introduces a maintenance hazard (e.g. adding a public URL in the security config but forgetting the filter's method).
* **Recommendation:** Remove `shouldNotFilter` entirely from the JWT filter class and let Spring Security's request matchers manage authentication bypass.

### 4. Virtual Threads Disabled (Java 21 Thread Optimization)
* **File:** [application.properties](file:///c:/Users/YashRanjan/Desktop/Software%20Consulting/03_Projects/enterprise-asset-management-system/backend/src/main/resources/application.properties)
* **Description:** 
  The project runs on Java 21 and Spring Boot 3.x, but does not take advantage of Virtual Threads. Without configuration, Spring Boot defaults to a platform-based pool of 200 threads.
* **Recommendation:** Enable virtual threads by adding `spring.threads.virtual.enabled=true` in `application.properties`. This allows the server to handle thousands of concurrent requests with minimal memory overhead.

### 5. Missing Swagger UI Security Schemes
* **File:** [OpenApiConfig.java](file:///c:/Users/YashRanjan/Desktop/Software%20Consulting/03_Projects/enterprise-asset-management-system/backend/src/main/java/com/yashconsulting/eams/config/OpenApiConfig.java)
* **Description:** 
  The OpenAPI setup does not configure security definitions. As a result, Swagger UI lacks an "Authorize" option, which prevents developers and QA teams from testing authenticated endpoints (like `/api/v1/users`) from the browser.
* **Recommendation:** Define a `SecurityScheme` of type HTTP Bearer JWT and apply a global `SecurityRequirement` to the `OpenAPI` Bean.

### 6. Manual DTO Mapping Boilerplate
* **File:** [UserMapper.java](file:///c:/Users/YashRanjan/Desktop/Software%20Consulting/03_Projects/enterprise-asset-management-system/backend/src/main/java/com/yashconsulting/eams/user/mapper/UserMapper.java)
* **Description:** 
  Mappings between entities and DTOs are written manually. This increases boilerplate and is error-prone (fields added to the database model can easily be missed in manual mapping code).
* **Recommendation:** Adopt MapStruct. Mappers can be defined as interfaces, and implementation classes will be automatically generated during compilation.

